msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Collection of works copied by Charles Rainsford that includes texts on the Druze people and their religion, classical philosophers, and a final section of medical recipes and remedies. Also includes a partial list of contents (p. 30). There is a cracked but intact red wax seal on p. 80.
msContents.textLang: English, with some Greek and a few words in Hebrew

author.name: Charles Rainsford Collection of Alchemical and Occult Manuscripts (University of Pennsylvania)

supportDesc.extent: 138 leaves : 193 x 158 (165 x 115) mm bound to 200 x 168 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 138 leaves; [1-240, 1-3, 3-35]; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script in the hand of Charles Rainsford.

origin.p: Written in Gibraltar[?] in the second half of the 18th century.

history.provenance: Owned by the 2nd through 12th Dukes of Northumberland, ms. 610-614, Alnwick Castle, Northumberland, 1809-2014 (bookplate, inside upper cover; stamps throughout).
Formerly owned by Charles Rainsford (British army officer, fellow of the Royal Society, and alchemist); bequeathed by Rainsford to Hugh Percy, Second Duke of Northumberland.
Sold at auction at Sotheby's (London), 15 July 2014, as part of Lot 411.
